AWKA – The Anambra State Police Command has arrested a 27-year-old lady,  Ozioma Orakwe for the suspected murder of his uncle. Ozioma was arrested following suspicion that her uncle, 75-year-old Martin Orakwe who was said to have committed suicide may have been killed. Photograph of late Mr. Orakwe’s dangling body tied to a rope by the neck had the previous day gone viral. 32-Year-Old Teacher Arrested For Defiling 6-Year-Old Girl In… Man Arrested For Allegedly Raping 80-Year- Old Woman In Nasarawa However, according to a statement issued by the Police Public Relations Officer, Ikenga Tochukwu, a Deputy Superintendent of Police, “preliminary investigation revealed that Mr. Anakwe had a cut on his head with marks of violence all over his body”. Additional information showed that before his death, he had some disagreement, maybe with Ozioma which resulted in a fight. Police operatives, the statement, said have recovered the body of the deceased and the suspect has also made a useful statement that is helping in the ongoing investigation after which the case shall be charged to court after a conclusive investigation, Ikenga said. The Commissioner of Police Echeng Echeng has, however, admonished citizens to always seek other means of settling their differences than resorting to violent fighting.